        "iCloud Drive" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Focuses on operating system level cloud syncronization features, such as iCloud Drive and OneDrive, which may be used to synchronize files between a local system and a cloud service." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1067" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Extract artifacts from operating system cloud synchronization features" .

:techniqueDFT-1068 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1068: Extract operating system artifacts indicating recently used files"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEInputClass "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/FileSet"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/accessedTime"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/filePath"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "The process of examining operating system files to extract artifacts that may indicate file accesses." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDetails "While this technique may result in file paths and timestamps, to evaluate a hypothesis that a file was accessed requires use of T1155 to evaluate if this access occurred, and optionally T1117 if the time of access is relevant." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1068" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Extract operating system artifacts indicating recently used files" .

