    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "A technique developed in Hargreaves & Marshall (2018) whereby synchronization artifacts on a device are examined and used to identify the existence of a related device. Also sometimes used to infer activity that occurred on an inaccessible or unavailable device. " ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1007" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Detect the potential existence of digital devices using a SyncTriage-based approach" .

:techniqueDFT-1010 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1010: Place device in a faraday environment"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEInputClass "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/Device"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/Device"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialWeakness :weaknessDFW-1115,
        :weaknessDFW-1116,
        :weaknessDFW-1117 ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1086 ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Place a device in an environment designed to shield a mobile phone or small digital device from radio waves entering the environment and reaching the device, and to stop radio waves escaping from the environment (adapted from Lennox-Steele & Nisbet (2016))" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDetails "Environment should block: mobile network, Wi-Fi, and Bluetooth and all other RF." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1010" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Place device in a faraday environment" .

:techniqueDFT-1013 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1013: Write protect storage media using a software write blocker"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEInputClass "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/ReadWriteDeviceInterface"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/WriteProtectedDeviceInterface"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/WriteProtectedDeviceInterface"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1102 ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Use of a software-based tool that prevents a computer from writing to computer storage media connected to it (NIST 2006)" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDetails "Note that both read/write and write protected interfaces are specified as input since a software write blocker could be applied to a hardware write protected interface." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1013" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Write protect storage media using a software write blocker" .

:techniqueDFT-1020 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1020: Extract the file system from a mobile device"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEInputClass "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/MobileDevice"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/FileSystemExtraction"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialWeakness :weaknessDFW-1159,
        :weaknessDFW-1160,
        :weaknessDFW-1161,
        :weaknessDFW-1162,
        :weaknessDFW-1163,
        :weaknessDFW-1164 ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1031,
        :citationDFCite-1045,
        :citationDFCite-1091 ;
    solveit-core:hasSynonym "file system extraction" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Accessing the file system(s) of the device and extracting a set of files (full or partial depending on level of access)" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDetails "Note that Fukami et al (2021) states \"In order to conduct effective file system extraction, rooting the device is required.\" See T1040. Usually results in a zip/tar file. Rooting may provide access to the file system, but files may still be encrypted. Attacking the user pin, usually on device, using T1034, or T1035 may be necessary, unless the PIN can be obtained from the device user (T1037)" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1020" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Extract the file system from a mobile device" .

:techniqueDFT-1033 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1033: Extract credential(s) from an accessible device to attempt access to a more secure device or service"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/Credential"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Accessing a device with limited or no security to obtain a credential (e.g. password, PIN, token) that can be used to access another device or service." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1033" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Extract credential(s) from an accessible device to attempt access to a more secure device or service" .

:techniqueDFT-1042 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1042: Verify hash of imaged data matches the hash of the source device"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEInputClass "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/hash"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/HashVerificationResult"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialWeakness :weaknessDFW-1042,
        :weaknessDFW-1124,
        :weaknessDFW-1125,
        :weaknessDFW-1126,
        :weaknessDFW-1127,
        :weaknessDFW-1128 ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1081,
        :citationDFCite-1083,
        :citationDFCite-1088 ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1042" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Verify hash of imaged data matches the hash of the source device" .

:techniqueDFT-1090 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1090: Experiment with software to ascertain forensic artifacts"@en ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "The process of running software in a controlled environment to observe its behavior and identify potential forensic artifacts." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDetails "The equivalent of `dynamic analysis` of malware, but applied to software in general. This can involve running the software in a controlled environment and observing its behavior, inputs, and outputs to gain insights into its functionality and potential for event reconstruction." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1090" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Experiment with software to ascertain forensic artifacts" .

:techniqueDFT-1099 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1099: Repair a damaged or incomplete file using `grafting`"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEInputClass "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/ContentData"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/File"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Repair file by grafting different reference data onto fragment(s)" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1099" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Repair a damaged or incomplete file using `grafting`" .

:techniqueDFT-1105 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1105: Examine memory dump from an application"@en ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Examination of the specific structures from the memory of a specific application" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDetails "These could be extracted from a physical memory dump through analysis of operating system memory structures to extract specific process memory, or obtained directly on a live system." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1105" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Examine memory dump from an application" .

:techniqueDFT-1110 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1110: Preserve reference data"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialWeakness :weaknessDFW-1172 ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1118 ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDetails "Reference data may be needed for later trace interpretation, but may change (especially server side software), so relevant data should be preserved close to the time of the event of interest" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1110" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Preserve reference data" .

:techniqueDFT-1111 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1111: Record system clock offset"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEInputClass "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/Device"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/ClockOffsetCapture"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/systemTime"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialWeakness :weaknessDFW-1173 ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Recording a system clock compared with trusted time source" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDetails "Collection of the time of a device clock compared with the correct time, allowing an offset to be calculated *for the point in time when the clock was observed*." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1111" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Record system clock offset" .

:techniqueDFT-1113 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1113: Access internal storage via bootable environment"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEInputClass "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/Computer"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/ReadWriteDeviceInterface"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasExample "PALADIN Forensic - is a modified “live” Linux distribution based on Ubuntu that simplifies various forensics tasks in a forensically sound manner via the PALADIN Toolbox.",
        "WinFE - Windows Forensic Environment, is forensically sound, bootable Windows operation system that can be burned into USB and plug the USB into suspected device. Then, after changing boot order, booting to the USB to create forensic images from the tested Windows, MacOS and Linux systems." ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialWeakness :weaknessDFW-1177,
        :weaknessDFW-1178,
        :weaknessDFW-1179,
        :weaknessDFW-1180,
        :weaknessDFW-1182 ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1071,
        :citationDFCite-1112,
        :citationDFCite-1132 ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Booting the suspected computer device into an alternative operating system in order to image the attached disks." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDetails "These operating systems are usually modified to contain forensic imaging tools and to avoid writing to the attached storage through the use of software write blocking (DFT-1013)" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1113" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Access internal storage via bootable environment" .

:techniqueDFT-1119 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1119: Automatically scan for artifact changes caused by app updates"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/TableField"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/filePath"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/hasChanged"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/observable/tableSchema"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasExample "Discussed in 'Puma: Automatically generating digital forensic reference data triggered by mobile application updates' (Claij-Swart et al. 2025)" ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialWeakness :weaknessDFW-1191 ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1033,
        :citationDFCite-1034 ;
    solveit-core:hasSynonym "App update monitoring" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Monitor every version change of an application to determine if there are changes to the way the app stores data" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1119" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Automatically scan for artifact changes caused by app updates" .

:techniqueDFT-1127 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1127: Keyword search (live) (logical)"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/KeywordSearchResult"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialWeakness :weaknessDFW-1195 ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1103,
        :citationDFCite-1133 ;
    solveit-core:hasSynonym "live search" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Searching for keywords over the raw data, without an index of text content, but on a file by file basis" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDetails "This approach can include decoding the individual file formats and content. It can also overcome limitations associated with compressed data or data split due to file fragmentation." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1127" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Keyword search (live) (logical)" .

:techniqueDFT-1129 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1129: Search for indicators of clock tampering"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1039,
        :citationDFCite-1127 ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Searching for indicators that the system clock has been tampered with" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1129" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Search for indicators of clock tampering" .

:techniqueDFT-1134 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1134: Use time anchors to estimate clock offset"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEInputClass "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/DateTimeStamp"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/TimestampOffset"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasExample "Browser caches often contain local timestamps and those derived from external servers",
        "Email headers often record timestamps derived from external mail servers as well as timestamps generated by the local system time",
        "Missed call or voicemail notification messages often include a timestamp derived from an external time source, e.g., missed call from XX on 2018-06-06 at 01:32:49 pm, which can be compared to the local file system time the message was received",
        "Records in web browser history databases contain local timestamps and, in some cases, timestamps from external servers, embedded in URLs" ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialWeakness :weaknessDFW-1260,
        :weaknessDFW-1261,
        :weaknessDFW-1262,
        :weaknessDFW-1263 ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1020 ;
    solveit-core:hasSynonym "Time anchoring (Vanini et al 2024)",
        "Timestamp correlation" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Correlate timestamps from the system clock and an external trusted time source (Time Anchoring)" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDetails "Correlate timestamps from the system clock and an external trusted source of time contained in the same artifact, allowing an offset to be estimated *for the point in time the timestamp was recorded*" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1134" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Use time anchors to estimate clock offset" .

:techniqueDFT-1144 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1144: Enumerate browser profiles"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialWeakness :weaknessDFW-1249 ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "The enumeration of the separate user profiles set up within a browser" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1144" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Enumerate browser profiles" .

:techniqueDFT-1153 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1153: Apply offset to a timestamp"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasCASEOutputClass "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/DateTimeStamp"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://ontology.solveit-df.org/solveit/observable/TimelineEntry"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialWeakness :weaknessDFW-1264,
        :weaknessDFW-1265,
        :weaknessDFW-1267,
        :weaknessDFW-1268 ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Application of a time offset to a timestamp" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDetails "This could be a clock offset, a timezone or other reason for a timestamp correction" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1153" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Apply offset to a timestamp" .

:techniqueDFT-1158 a solveit-core:Technique ;
    rdfs:label "DFT-1158: Configure device to enable a service needed for data extraction"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasExample "Turn on developer mode to make use of Android Debug Bridge (ADB)" ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialWeakness :weaknessDFW-1274 ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1004 ;
    solveit-core:techniqueDescription "Change a setting on a device such that a service needed for data extraction is enabled. This may require a user PIN that can be obtained using other techniques." ;
    solveit-core:techniqueID "DFT-1158" ;
    solveit-core:techniqueName "Configure device to enable a service needed for data extraction" .

:weaknessDFW-1011 a solveit-core:Weakness ;
    rdfs:label "DFW-1011: Suggesting the existence of a device that does not exist"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialMitigation :mitigationDFM-1027,
        :mitigationDFM-1058 ;
    solveit-core:hasWeaknessClass solveit-core:ASTM_INAC_EX ;
    solveit-core:weaknessID "DFW-1011" ;
    solveit-core:weaknessName "Suggesting the existence of a device that does not exist" .

:weaknessDFW-1032 a solveit-core:Weakness ;
    rdfs:label "DFW-1032: Not all memory is acquired"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1128 ;
    solveit-core:hasWeaknessClass solveit-core:ASTM_INCOMP ;
    solveit-core:weaknessID "DFW-1032" ;
    solveit-core:weaknessName "Not all memory is acquired" .

:weaknessDFW-1037 a solveit-core:Weakness ;
    rdfs:label "DFW-1037: Presenting data as complete, that is in reality a partial set"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialMitigation :mitigationDFM-1016,
        :mitigationDFM-1020 ;
    solveit-core:hasWeaknessClass solveit-core:ASTM_MISINT ;
    solveit-core:weaknessID "DFW-1037" ;
    solveit-core:weaknessName "Presenting data as complete, that is in reality a partial set" .

:weaknessDFW-1040 a solveit-core:Weakness ;
    rdfs:label "DFW-1040: Not considering SD Card acquisition in addition to other extractions performed"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialMitigation :mitigationDFM-1017,
        :mitigationDFM-1018 ;
    solveit-core:hasWeaknessClass solveit-core:ASTM_INCOMP ;
    solveit-core:weaknessID "DFW-1040" ;
    solveit-core:weaknessName "Not considering SD Card acquisition in addition to other extractions performed" .

:weaknessDFW-1041 a solveit-core:Weakness ;
    rdfs:label "DFW-1041: Not considering file system acquisition as alternative"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialMitigation :mitigationDFM-1019 ;
    solveit-core:hasWeaknessClass solveit-core:ASTM_INCOMP ;
    solveit-core:weaknessID "DFW-1041" ;
    solveit-core:weaknessName "Not considering file system acquisition as alternative" .

:weaknessDFW-1059 a solveit-core:Weakness ;
    rdfs:label "DFW-1059: Excessive keyword results returned from case-type wordlists such that careful review of all results is impractical"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialMitigation :mitigationDFM-1032,
        :mitigationDFM-1033,
        :mitigationDFM-1038 ;
    solveit-core:hasWeaknessClass solveit-core:ASTM_INCOMP ;
    solveit-core:weaknessID "DFW-1059" ;
    solveit-core:weaknessName "Excessive keyword results returned from case-type wordlists such that careful review of all results is impractical" .

:weaknessDFW-1132 a solveit-core:Weakness ;
    rdfs:label "DFW-1132: Incorrectly computing the hash of one or more files within a disk image due to incorrect hash algorithm implementation"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1060 ;
    solveit-core:hasWeaknessClass solveit-core:ASTM_INAC_ALT,
        solveit-core:ASTM_INAC_AS ;
    solveit-core:weaknessID "DFW-1132" ;
    solveit-core:weaknessName "Incorrectly computing the hash of one or more files within a disk image due to incorrect hash algorithm implementation" .

:weaknessDFW-1148 a solveit-core:Weakness ;
    rdfs:label "DFW-1148: Timestamp used is an inaccurate representation of the real world time due to inaccurate system clock"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialMitigation :mitigationDFM-1101,
        :mitigationDFM-1225,
        :mitigationDFM-1227,
        :mitigationDFM-1228 ;
    solveit-core:hasWeaknessClass solveit-core:ASTM_INAC_EX ;
    solveit-core:weaknessID "DFW-1148" ;
    solveit-core:weaknessName "Timestamp used is an inaccurate representation of the real world time due to inaccurate system clock" .

:weaknessDFW-1150 a solveit-core:Weakness ;
    rdfs:label "DFW-1150: Misinterpreting events from automated processes as user generated ones"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasReference :citationDFCite-1073 ;
    solveit-core:hasWeaknessClass solveit-core:ASTM_INAC_EX,
        solveit-core:ASTM_MISINT ;
    solveit-core:weaknessID "DFW-1150" ;
    solveit-core:weaknessName "Misinterpreting events from automated processes as user generated ones" .

:weaknessDFW-1195 a solveit-core:Weakness ;
    rdfs:label "DFW-1195: Keyword results from a tool are associated with a file, but the result was within slack space and therefore it may not have been part of that file"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialMitigation :mitigationDFM-1151 ;
    solveit-core:hasWeaknessClass solveit-core:ASTM_INAC_AS,
        solveit-core:ASTM_MISINT ;
    solveit-core:weaknessID "DFW-1195" ;
    solveit-core:weaknessName "Keyword results from a tool are associated with a file, but the result was within slack space and therefore it may not have been part of that file" .

:weaknessDFW-1266 a solveit-core:Weakness ;
    rdfs:label "DFW-1266: Timestamp used is an inaccurate representation of the real world time due to timezone and/or daylight savings"@en ;
    solveit-core:hasPotentialMitigation :mitigationDFM-1101,
        :mitigationDFM-1224,
        :mitigationDFM-1229,
        :mitigationDFM-1230 ;
    solveit-core:hasWeaknessClass solveit-core:ASTM_INAC_EX ;
    solveit-core:weaknessID "DFW-1266" ;
    solveit-core:weaknessName "Timestamp used is an inaccurate representation of the real world time due to timezone and/or daylight savings" .

:citationDFCite-1004 a solveit-core:Citation ;
    rdfs:label "DFCite-1004" ;
    solveit-core:citationID "DFCite-1004" ;
    solveit-core:citationPlaintext "Android (2025), How to Enable Android Developer Settings: Unlock your Device’s Hidden Potential, https://www.android.com/intl/en_uk/articles/enable-android-developer-settings/" .

